[{"id":"VR619227","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. The figure on the left shows a block of mass m at rest at the center of a horizontal platform. Two ropes are connected to either end of the platform, which meet at a point located far above the center of the  block. The rope then extends vertically upward. The figure on the right shows a free body diagram with four arrows extending from a dot in a gridded plane. The first arrow is labeled T and extends upward and to the left until it ends at a point that is 2 units to the left, and 2 units above the dot. The second arrow is labeled T and extends upward and to the right until it ends at a point that is 2 units to the right, and 2 units above the dot. The third and fourth arrows extend vertically downward one unit. The third arrow is labeled F sub N, and the fourth arrow is labeled F sub g.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR619227.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A platform of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is held at rest by two ropes connected to its ends, as shown in the diagram on the left. A block, also of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span>, is placed on the center of the platform. A student draws a free-body diagram representing the forces exerted on the platform while it is at rest, as shown in the diagram on the right. Which of the following claims best explains why the diagram is incorrect?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR619227_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The tension forces from the ropes do not point in the correct directions.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The diagram does not include components of the tension forces in the ropes.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The horizontal forces are unbalanced.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The vertical forces are unbalanced.</p>"],"answer":3}]